{"word":"ἄθεος","slug":"ἄθεος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄθεος</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>without God, denying the gods</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>godless, ungodly</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Comparative'>comp.</a> <el>-ώτερος</el> <b><a href='S:Lysias'>Lys.</a></b>; <a href='S:Superlative'>Sup.</a> <el>-ώτατος</el> <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>abandoned of the gods</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-ως</el>, <i>impiously</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <a href='S:Superlative'>Sup.</a> <el>-ώτατα</el>, <i>in most unholy wise</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}